{"id":13006,"date":"2024-01-27T03:03:23","date_gmt":"2024-01-27T03:03:23","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/?p=13006"},"modified":"2024-02-20T23:19:29","modified_gmt":"2024-02-20T23:19:29","slug":"in-one-year-new-york-citys-messaging-went-from-you-do-you-to-mask-up-with-an-n95","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/in-one-year-new-york-citys-messaging-went-from-you-do-you-to-mask-up-with-an-n95\/","title":{"rendered":"In One Year, New York City&#8217;s Messaging Went from &#8220;You do You&#8221; to &#8220;Mask up with an N95.&#8221;"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<div class=\"wp-container-1 wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\"><\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-container-6 wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-container-5 wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:100%\">\n<div class=\"wp-container-4 wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-container-2 wp-block-column\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"550\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">In one year, New York City&#39;s messaging went from &quot;you do you&quot; to &quot;mask up with an N95.&quot;<br><br>This didn&#39;t happen by chance. Advocates &amp; groups like <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/COVIDAdvocacyNY?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@COVIDAdvocacyNY<\/a> organized to take down the MTA signs &amp; attended every NYC hearing on COVID to push for better messaging. Advocacy works! <a href=\"https:\/\/t.co\/NPwAKq9r7w\">pic.twitter.com\/NPwAKq9r7w<\/a><\/p>&mdash; Dr. Lucky Tran (@luckytran) <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/luckytran\/status\/1737201157045424363?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">December 19, 2023<\/a><\/blockquote><script async src=\"https:\/\/platform.twitter.com\/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"><\/script>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-container-3 wp-block-column\">\n<p>Dr. Lucky Tran, a public health and climate justice advocate and science communicator, took to X to compare mask signage created by the Metropolitan Transit Authority. On the left is a sign from September 2022 that implies that any way travelers wear a mask is ok even if that\u2019s incorrect. On the right is a post from&nbsp;<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/nycHealthy\" target=\"_blank\">@nycHealthy<\/a>&nbsp;that emphasizes the ways masks are for the public good by protecting the wearer and the people around them. Dr. Tran promotes the work of&nbsp;<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/COVIDAdvocacyNY\" target=\"_blank\">@COVIDAdvocacyNY,&nbsp;<\/a>a group dedicated to&nbsp;attending NYC COVID-19 hearings and asking for better signage. Covid Advocacy NY, formerly &#8220;Mandate Masks NY&#8221; is an &#8220;advocacy&nbsp;group led by concerned New Yorkers to get NYC &amp; NY to provide free masks, mandate masks when needed, &amp; save lives from Covid.\u201d <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>COVID-19 has faded to the back of people&#8217;s minds as it has been less prominent in news headlines. This has led to companies relaxing all of their mask policies. Disabled activists and groups like COVID Advocacy work to remind the public that COVID is still ever present, especially in winter 2023 as the <a href=\"https:\/\/ny1.com\/nyc\/all-boroughs\/health\/2023\/12\/20\/jn-1-covid-19-subvariant\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">JN1 variant spiked in NYC<\/a>. As Dr. Tran pointed out, their advocacy succeeded!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>-Stephanie Farmer<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Dr. Lucky Tran, a public health and climate justice advocate and science communicator, took to X to compare mask signage created by the Metropolitan Transit Authority. On the left is a sign from September 2022 that implies that any way travelers wear a mask is ok even if that\u2019s incorrect.&hellip; <a class=\"continue\" href=\"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/in-one-year-new-york-citys-messaging-went-from-you-do-you-to-mask-up-with-an-n95\/\">Continue Reading<span> In One Year, New York City&#8217;s Messaging Went from &#8220;You do You&#8221; to &#8220;Mask up with an N95.&#8221;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":4,"featured_media":13003,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"advanced_seo_description":"","jetpack_seo_html_title":"","jetpack_seo_noindex":false,"_FSMCFIC_featured_image_caption":"MTA mask signage","_FSMCFIC_featured_image_nocaption":"","_FSMCFIC_featured_image_hide":""},"categories":[44],"tags":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Screen-Shot-2024-01-26-at-2.52.03-PM-1.png?fit=1154%2C652&ssl=1","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/13006"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/4"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=13006"}],"version-history":[{"count":14,"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/13006\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":13093,"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/13006\/revisions\/13093"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/13003"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=13006"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=13006"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=13006"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}